From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Batocera <batocera@localhost>
Date: Sun, 17 May 2026 07:18:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] unarr: do not force LTO

Buildroot's CMake toolchain uses the target ar/ranlib for static
archives.  The vendored unarr CMakeLists unconditionally adds -flto,
which can leave libunarr.a with LTO members that are not pulled in when
NanoBoyAdvance links its Qt executable.

The final link then sees unresolved ar_* symbols from platform-core even
though libunarr.a is present on the command line.  Let the package build
without unarr-local LTO so the static archive links normally.
---
 thirdparty/unarr-1.1.1-patch/CMakeLists.txt | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/thirdparty/unarr-1.1.1-patch/CMakeLists.txt b/thirdparty/unarr-1.1.1-patch/CMakeLists.txt
index 514e82f..cbb47ab 100644
--- a/thirdparty/unarr-1.1.1-patch/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/thirdparty/unarr-1.1.1-patch/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -194,8 +194,7 @@ if(UNIX
             -Werror-implicit-function-declaration
             $<$<CONFIG:Release>:-fomit-frame-pointer>
             $<$<C_COMPILER_ID:Clang,AppleClang>:
-            -Wno-missing-field-initializers>
-            -flto)
+            -Wno-missing-field-initializers>)
   if(BUILD_FUZZER)
     target_compile_options(unarr PUBLIC "${sanitize_opts}")
     target_compile_definitions(
-- 
